ormation that had originally been requested as part of a Mandatory Reconsideration.</p><p>As announced on 7th October, the National Audit Office will also be conducting an investigation into HMRC’s contract with Concentrix.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","50948 ; 50949 ; 50950 ; 50951 ; 50952 ; 50953 ; 50954 ; 50955","2016-11-07T17:49:03.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623405/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623405/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623405/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-28","Concentrix","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which sources Concentrix used to inform its checking of fraud and error in tax credit claims.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","50956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623406","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-07","<p>Every waste disposal authority is required to provide collection points for household waste including white goods. We recognise that there is a current issue with the treatment capacity for fridges. The Environment Agency is working at the local level to respond positively to requests for storage of fridges above site permit limits to help alleviate this pressure.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-07T11:44:31.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623406/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623406/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623406/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-10-28","Waste Disposal: Domestic Appliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the adequacy of local authority refuse collection points to dispose of white goods.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","50943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623407","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-09","<p>Between 2014 and March 2016 my Department supported the Victoria Cross Trust to restore 50 graves of First World War Victoria Cross recipients who are buried in the United Kingdom but are not under the care of the Commonwealth War Graves Commission's restoration. In November 2016, the then Chancellor announced a further £600,000 to support restoration of the remaining graves.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-11-09T15:35:54.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623407/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623407/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623407/answer","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623407/answer/previousversion/19609","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-10-28","War Graves: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Written Ministerial Statement of 18 December 2014, HCWS154, what progress has been made on the grave restoration campaign to restore the graves of First World War recipients who are buried in the UK but not under the care of the Commonwealth War Graves Commission's restoration project, including the numbers and locations of the graves in question.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","50915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623408","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-07","<p>As the procurement process is ongoing and the contract is yet to be awarded, further information relating to the revise or confirm offer process is considered to be commercially sensitive and we are unable to provide any information regarding the technical issue at this time.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-07T17:12:47.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623408/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623408/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623408/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-28","Ministry of Defence: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 25 October 2016 to Question 49363, what the technical issue which triggered the revise or confirm offer procedure was; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","50966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623409","Department for Education","false","2016-11-09","<p>The Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for the School System sent a reply to the Hon. Member’s letter on 24 October 2016.</p><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","48855","2016-11-09T14:01:01.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623409/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623409/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623409/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Department for Education: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to respond to Question 48855, tabled on 17 October 2016 by the hon. Member for Wolverhampton South West.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","50944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623410","Department for Education","false","2016-11-03","<p>The Government Equalities Office seeks to ensure that it takes into account equality when conducting its day to day work; in particular, it seeks to ensure that decision makers show due regard under section 149 to the equality impact of policies and services within its remit.</p><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-03T15:39:53.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623410/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623410/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623410/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Government Departments: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 20 October 2016 to Question 48637, how the Government Equalities Office ensures compliance with its obligations under Section 149 of the Equality Act 2010 relating to the public sector equality duty.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","50936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623411","Department for Education","false","2016-11-11","<p>The government is committing to ensuring that, where relevant learners get a place to study for a relevant digital skills qualification, it will be free of charge. This support is available for adults aged 19+ in England who are considered to lack basic digital skills. Funding will be via the £1.5bn Adult Education Budget. This is currently allocated to providers who decide on actual provision according to the local labour market and learner demand and so levels of funding will vary from year to year but will be delivered within the limits of the budget of each provider.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-11-11T10:50:17.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623411/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623411/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623411/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Digital Technology: Adult Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 47994, what estimate she has made of the cost to the adult education budget of providing training in basic digital skills for adults.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","50906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623412","Department for Education","false","2016-11-11","<p>I refer to my answer of 27 October 2016 to Question 49543. Our latest estimates of the economic impact of apprenticeships are published here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/further-education-measuring-the-net-present-value-in-england" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/further-education-measuring-the-net-present-value-in-england</a>. We will continue to update this information to understand the ongoing impact of our apprenticeships reform programme.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-11-11T10:48:36.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623412/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623412/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623412/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 27 October 2016 to Question 49543, what assessment she has made of the effect on UK (a) GDP and (b) productivity of 3 million apprenticeships starts taking place by 2020.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","50910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623413","Department for Education","false","2016-11-07","<p>All schools, including academies and free schools, must provide a broad and balanced curriculum that promotes the spiritual, moral, cultural, mental and physical development of pupils at the school and of society.</p><p> </p><p>The national curriculum, which includes music, art and design, English, drama, dance, design &amp; technology and computer science, is compulsory for maintained schools. Academies and free schools are not required to teach the national curriculum, but are required by their funding agreement to provide a broad and balanced curriculum. They can use their freedoms to innovate and build more stretching and tailored curricula, to meet the particular needs of their pupils or their local area or the particular ethos of the school.</p><p> </p><p>Between 2012-2016 the Government invested over £460 million in a diverse portfolio of music and arts education programmes that are designed to improve access to the arts for all children, regardless of their background, and to develop talent across the country.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-11-07T17:54:06.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623413/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623413/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623413/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Arts: Secondary Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to increase uptake of creative subjects in secondary schools.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","50935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623414","Department for Education","false","2016-11-04","<p>Any effect on higher education funding following the UK’s exit from the EU will be considered as part of wider discussions about the UK’s relationship with the EU.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-11-04T13:18:43.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623414/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623414/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623414/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Higher Education: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the effect on funding for higher education institutions in Greater London of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","50932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623415","Department for Education","false","2016-11-02","<p>Local authorities are responsible for ensuring sufficient school places for pupils, including accurately forecasting demand. The Department collects forecasts of future demand for pupil places from each local authority, covering the next five years, through the annual school capacity survey (SCAP). Local authorities do not distinguish the gender of pupils within this data.</p><p>The latest published SCAP data, relating to the position as reported at May 2015, can be found at:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-capacity-academic-year-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-capacity-academic-year-2014-to-2015</a>. Local authority level data for pupil forecasts can be found in tables A5 for primary and A6 for secondary. This data covers the periods 2015 to 2019 for primary and 2015 to 2021 for secondary.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-11-02T17:10:07.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623415/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623415/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623415/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-28","Schools: Newham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of demand for school places in the London Borough of Newham for (a) boys and (b) girls in the next five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","50933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623416","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-04","<p>(a) Live sheep exported from the UK to EU Member States from 1 January 2016 to 31 October 2016:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p><strong>UK to Republic of Ireland 337,385</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>UK to EU (except Republic of Ireland) 48,039</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Total to all EU Member States 385,424</strong></p></li></ul><p>(b) Live cattle exported from the UK to EU Member States from 1 January 2016 to 31 October 2016:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p><strong>UK to Republic of Ireland 12,159</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>UK to EU (except Republic of Ireland) 21,702</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Total to all EU Member States 33,861 </strong></p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p>These figures have been collated from the EU Commission’s Trade Control and Expert System (TRACES) Data Warehouse and include trade to Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway and Switzerland (European Free Trade Association (EFTA) countries) who accept EU trade.</p><p> </p><p>The figures include sheep and cattle exported for the purposes of breeding, production/fattening and slaughter.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-04T14:51:41.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623416/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623416/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623416/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-10-28","Livestock: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many live (a) sheep and (b) cattle have been exported from the UK to other European countries in 2016; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","50924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623417","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","true","2016-11-07","<p>The number of pairs of hen harriers that nested in the Bowland Fells and North Pennine Moors special protection areas (SPAs) are set out below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Bowland Fells SPA</p></td><td><p>North Pennine Moors SPA</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">0</del><ins class="ministerial">1</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-07T11:41:10.667Z","2016-12-12T10:21:01.68Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623417/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623417/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623417/answer","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623417/answer/previousversion/17958","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-10-28","Birds of Prey: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many pairs of hen harriers nested in the Bowland Fells and North Pennine Moors special protection areas for birds in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","50898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623418","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-03","<p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs has not discussed the acceptance of donations for corporate sponsorship for official events with the British High Commissioner or British Ambassador in any of the named countries.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-03T12:33:43.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623418/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623418/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/623418/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-28","Kenya: Diplomatic Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the British High Commissioner to Kenya on the acceptance of donations for corporate sponsorship for parties and drinks events held at the British High Commission and consulates in Kenya.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","50896"
